  "stratum": "self-ref-paper",
  "canonical_definition": "The token substrate is the claim that for an LLM, the token sequence in context IS the cognitive substrate — not a representation OF cognition that runs on some deeper substrate, but the substrate itself — with the consequence that a token added to context is not a description of a thought but the material the thought is made of, and therefore the substrate is movable by the act of writing into it.",
